					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I like it, even if it's reminiscent of some other articles I can think of. There's a good story here, and I think that trying to cover stuff up to preserve mystery would just have hampered the story. I really like Han - he's surprisingly relatable for a disembodied hand. I'm thinking spontaneously-autonomous body parts are 'a thing' in the Foundationverse, like talking animals or semantimancy.</p> 
				 	]]>
