					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-997140#post-2095398</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-997140/scp-2913#post-2095398</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 23 Aug 2014 15:31:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doctor Cimmerian</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1414765</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Since it seems to be mostly alright with the number(I mean it's nothing serious) it's just easier to not call him Han. Not to mention the obvious joke it's trying to make. That said I've edited it to &quot;Heya Maddox&quot; from &quot;Hi Doc&quot;. Should be more natural, but just as informal as I was going for? And thanks for the upvote. ;)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-997140#post-2095381</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-997140/scp-2913#post-2095381</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 23 Aug 2014 14:57:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Smapti</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>362048</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Is there any reason they <em>wouldn't</em> address him as &quot;Han&quot; during interviews if it makes him comfortable and gets useful information out of him? The fact that 2913 is the official designation for documents doesn't mean that the doctors have to browbeat him into saying he's a number and not a human <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">being</span> sapient hand thing.</p> <p>Also, I don't think I've ever heard anyone address a doctor as &quot;Doc&quot; in real life, and it always comes off as artificial when I see it used here.</p> <p>Anyway, good twist on an old concept. Upvoted.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
